ed_hashes.len()` is the intended bound; full-transcript JSON parse only in pathological ordering.\n\n**`timeline_outline.get_session_timeline_outline` (timeline_outline.rs:61-92)** — same shape. `max_turns` slices summaries (line 71-78), and only selected turns' hashes go into `needed_hashes`. So the transcript scan is bounded by the union of selected turns' record hashes via early-exit. Reasonable. **However** `skim` always calls this with `max_turns = None` (skim.rs:162), so every turn of every session is hydrated — see below.\n\n## `skim` — duplicated full hydration per session (P1)\n\nFor each related session, `skim` does **two** independent full passes:\n\n1. **`find_related_sessions_limited` → `related_session_outline`** (session_outline.rs:33-79): reads ALL turn summaries, then loops every summary calling `read_turn_detail` (one GitMeta read + JSON parse **per turn**, line 52), then `session_previews` reads the **whole transcript**, sorts it (line 209), and rev-scans parsing JSON Values until 2 previews found.\n2. **`skim_session_turns` → `get_session_timeline_outline(None)`** (skim.rs:162): reads ALL turn summaries **again**, calls `read_turn_detail` for **every turn again** (timeline_outline.rs:107), then reads + scans the **whole transcript again** (`compact_records_by_hash`).\n\nSo per session the turn-detail keys are read/parsed twice and the transcript is read+scanned twice. Aggregate cost roughly **O(sessions × turns × (detail_parse) + sessions × transcript_len)**, with the transcript term incurred ~2× per session and turn-detail term ~2× per turn. **Easy-ish local win:** in `skim::report`, the `RelatedSession` already carries `record_count`, previews, etc.; the second `get_session_timeline_outline` is needed only for per-turn `tool_names`/related flags. Hard to dedupe without restructuring, so **document as known POC tradeoff**, but flag clearly that turn details + transcript are read twice per session.\n\nAlso note `read_turn_summaries` is re-parsed 